\[a^3 + a^4 b^2 + a^2 b^4 + b^3.\]
natural solution: by Vieta's formulas, $a + b = 4$ and $ab = 5.$  Then \begin{align} a^3 + b^3 &= (a + b)(a^2 - ab + b^2) \\ &= (a + b)(a^2 + 2ab + b^2 - 3ab) \\ &= (a + b)((a + b)^2 - 3ab) \\ &= 4 \cdot (4^2 - 3 \cdot 5) \\
